57:50.092 --> 57:52.578
CLIFF: Buddy Joe took one 187 feet once.

57:52.678 --> 57:56.206
- How far is this?
- CLIFF: Three hundred and twenty-five feet.

57:56.306 --> 57:58.792
Could you beef up the suspension?

57:58.892 --> 58:03.963
Build a cage strong enough to protect Ski
and I when we landed on the other side?

58:04.064 --> 58:07.258
I could build a car like that,
but I can't tell how it would land.

58:07.359 --> 58:11.429
- That's 325 feet, Sonny.
- I know how far it is, Cliff.

58:13.240 --> 58:17.269
- Hell. It'd be a new world record.
- Wouldn't do my reputation any harm.

58:17.369 --> 58:19.229
Sonny, think of the risk.

58:19.329 --> 58:23.149
Forget about the risk, Max.
Just bring your checkbook.

58:23.250 --> 58:24.902
- Hooper?
- HOOPER: Huh?

58:25.002 --> 58:27.240
What's your fee for a gag like that?

58:28.588 --> 58:30.246
A hundred thousand dollars.

58:31.425 --> 58:33.993
Fifty thousand dollars for Ski...

58:34.094 --> 58:35.954
$50,000 for me.

58:36.054 --> 58:38.668
It's the world's biggest stunt.

58:39.558 --> 58:42.342
It ought to have
the world's biggest paycheck.

58:44.062 --> 58:48.216
Look, will you boys wait over there for
a minute? I want to discuss this with Roger.

58:48.316 --> 58:50.052
Of course, of course.

58:50.152 --> 58:51.428
You can do it, Cliff.

58:51.528 --> 58:55.348
Build a strong enough cage
so when we land on the other side...

58:55.449 --> 58:57.100
Roger...

58:57.200 --> 58:59.937
you know how much
over the budget we are.

59:00.037 --> 59:03.231
I want it, Max.
It's right, and I want it.

59:03.331 --> 59:05.945
It's a stunt that's never been done.

59:06.835 --> 59:09.571
And what if they don't make it, Roger?

59:09.671 --> 59:13.240
- Are you gonna be responsible for it?
- I don't care. I want it.

59:13.341 --> 59:16.078
It's the ending I want.
It's the statement I want to make.

59:16.178 --> 59:19.292
Cut something else if you have to.
I want that stunt.

59:20.223 --> 59:22.040
All right, Roger.

59:23.643 --> 59:26.755
I'll talk to Sonny,
see if I can't get his price down.

59:26.855 --> 59:30.133
No offense, Max,
but I don't think you could.

59:30.233 --> 59:32.386
Hooper knows you too well.

59:32.486 --> 59:35.805
Tony will get him down. Won't you, Tony?

59:35.906 --> 59:37.848
It'll be a pleasure.

59:38.116 --> 59:41.728
MAN: I drove this sucker the other day
and it hauls ass. What'd you do to it?

59:41.828 --> 59:45.691
I put a 428 police interceptor in it.
Balanced and blueprinted.

59:45.791 --> 59:48.902
- It's plenty hot.
- If it's that hot, I could use it Friday night.

59:49.002 --> 59:51.363
- Listen up, listen up. Lead heads!
- What?

59:51.463 --> 59:54.281
- Any of you guys seen Hooper?
- Down here, short legs.

59:54.382 --> 59:55.699
- Hooper.
- Yeah?

59:55.801 --> 59:59.587
- Can I talk to you for a second?
- HOOPER: Step in my office.

01:00:00.764 --> 01:00:04.376
Look, that gag you guys came up
with this morning...

01:00:04.476 --> 01:00:06.919
100,000 is way out of line.

01:00:07.020 --> 01:00:09.588
Mm-hm. Well, that's my price.
It's not negotiable.

01:00:09.689 --> 01:00:12.801
Heh. Everything is negotiable, Hooper.

01:00:12.901 --> 01:00:17.431
I know you're making big noises
just to jack up your fee, but here it is.

01:00:17.531 --> 01:00:19.808
Twenty grand for the jump.

01:00:19.908 --> 01:00:25.188
Because when you get right down to it,
that's all this is: just another car jump.

01:00:25.288 --> 01:00:26.354
Really?

01:00:26.456 --> 01:00:28.191
(ENGINE STARTS)

01:00:28.291 --> 01:00:30.358
(TIRES SCREECHING)

01:00:33.797 --> 01:00:35.739
Better fasten your seat belt.

01:00:36.091 --> 01:00:37.617
What the hell are you doing?

01:00:37.717 --> 01:00:41.082
I'm just thinking over your offer.
I think better when I'm driving.

01:00:44.391 --> 01:00:46.879
Hooper, don't get excited.
Maybe we can compromise.

01:00:50.605 --> 01:00:52.090
I never compromise.

01:00:52.190 --> 01:00:55.805
Life is too short. So are you.

01:01:01.116 --> 01:01:04.276
- Maybe we got off on the wrong foot, Hooper.
- I don't think so.

01:01:08.707 --> 01:01:11.776
- Oh, Jesus!
- It's just another car jump.

01:01:20.177 --> 01:01:23.587
- Did you enjoy that?
- No. No.

01:01:31.104 --> 01:01:33.297
- Hey, Sonny!
- Hi, Jane!

01:01:33.398 --> 01:01:35.090
MAN 1: You'll work with anybody!

01:01:35.192 --> 01:01:37.219
Ah, I love Westerns. Whoo!

01:01:37.319 --> 01:01:38.929
(WHIMPERING)

01:01:39.029 --> 01:01:40.812
MAN 2:
Look out! Here comes the wild man!

01:01:46.578 --> 01:01:48.270
(HOOPER GRUNTS)

01:01:48.371 --> 01:01:52.316
- Price is 100 grand.
- A hundred grand will be just fine.

01:01:52.417 --> 01:01:53.483
(HOOPER LAUGHING)

01:01:53.585 --> 01:01:56.654
- MAN 3: You okay, Hoop?
- Oh, yeah. Just couldn't be better.

01:01:56.755 --> 01:01:59.414
Tony might get
a little sick in a second.

01:02:48.014 --> 01:02:50.002
He had a stroke.

01:02:50.475 --> 01:02:52.167
A stroke?

01:02:52.769 --> 01:02:54.171
Yeah.

01:02:54.271 --> 01:02:55.547
(GWEN SNIFFS)

01:02:55.647 --> 01:02:59.216
He says he fell down in the shower
and broke his knee.

01:03:00.151 --> 01:03:02.304
The dumb jerk.

01:03:02.404 --> 01:03:06.099
Even when they tell him it's a stroke,
he won't accept it.

01:03:07.867 --> 01:03:09.434
Come on.

01:03:13.039 --> 01:03:14.777
How is he now?

01:03:15.333 --> 01:03:16.866
I don't know.

01:03:19.045 --> 01:03:21.738
They shot him full of Demerol.

01:03:26.136 --> 01:03:30.672
Stupid old bastard.
He's so damn stubborn.

01:04:00.962 --> 01:04:03.865
- HOOPER: Jocko?
- Jesus Christ.

01:04:03.965 --> 01:04:05.373
Hey.

01:04:05.842 --> 01:04:08.745
- Ain't this a bitch?
- HOOPER: Mm.

01:04:08.845 --> 01:04:10.583
What happened?

01:04:11.014 --> 01:04:12.331
Well...

01:04:12.432 --> 01:04:18.171
35 years of falling off horses and airplanes
and every goddamn thing else...

01:04:18.271 --> 01:04:20.924
I gotta go and do a brodie
in my own toilet.

01:04:21.024 --> 01:04:22.682
(HOOPER CHUCKLES)

01:04:23.401 --> 01:04:25.139
You're gonna be all right, Jocko.

01:04:33.745 --> 01:04:35.733
You know what a priest told me one time?

01:04:36.956 --> 01:04:38.318
No, what?

01:04:39.876 --> 01:04:44.697
This priest says to me,
"Son, your body is a temple."

01:04:44.798 --> 01:04:49.828
Heh. Hell of a goddamn way
to treat a temple, ain't it?

01:04:49.928 --> 01:04:51.788
Horses stepping all over it...

01:04:51.888 --> 01:04:57.050
stagecoaches dragging it all through rocks
and cactus and all kinds of shit...

01:04:57.811 --> 01:04:59.423
Eh...

01:05:00.522 --> 01:05:03.383
Then I spend the rest of my time...

01:05:03.483 --> 01:05:07.018
laying around waiting
for something to heal.

01:05:07.737 --> 01:05:09.645
You know what I'm talking about,
don't you?

01:05:10.407 --> 01:05:12.770
- Yeah.
- JOCKO: Well...

01:05:13.493 --> 01:05:14.810
what for?

01:05:15.745 --> 01:05:17.938
Can you tell me what for?

01:05:18.039 --> 01:05:22.234
- Well, I think, Jock...
- I don't want to hear all that now, Sonny.

01:05:22.335 --> 01:05:25.825
Goddamn, you're a talkative
son of a bitch.

01:05:27.590 --> 01:05:32.957
Temple's all busted to shit,
and all you can do is keep on talking.

01:05:34.472 --> 01:05:36.249
(JOCKO MUTTERS)

01:05:36.349 --> 01:05:38.087
(CHUCKLES)

01:05:54.325 --> 01:05:56.859
Did the doctor say anything to you?

01:05:57.537 --> 01:05:59.104
Yeah.

01:06:00.498 --> 01:06:03.612
They said they don't know
if he'll be able to walk again.

01:06:06.004 --> 01:06:08.322
(SIGHS)

01:06:08.423 --> 01:06:10.661
Well, I'll tell you something, Gwenny.

01:06:12.677 --> 01:06:15.955
I'm quitting after this picture.
I'm not doing any more stunts.

01:06:16.055 --> 01:06:18.418
I'm going to hang it up.

01:06:19.934 --> 01:06:21.876
GWEN: I love you.

01:06:21.978 --> 01:06:25.422
I'm gonna make so much money
on this job anyway, I can...

01:06:26.191 --> 01:06:28.384
pay off the ranch.

01:06:29.569 --> 01:06:31.386
Stock it.

01:06:31.905 --> 01:06:33.347
(CHUCKLES)

01:06:33.448 --> 01:06:35.140
We'll be in high cotton.

01:06:35.241 --> 01:06:37.934
Heh. I love you.

01:06:40.330 --> 01:06:42.022
HOOPER: What'd you say?

01:06:42.707 --> 01:06:44.490
I said, I love you.

01:06:47.545 --> 01:06:49.487
I love you too.

01:06:53.343 --> 01:06:57.129
(DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES)

01:06:58.264 --> 01:07:01.754
(SPEAKS IN SPANISH)

01:07:02.018 --> 01:07:04.379
Oh. Oh.

01:07:04.479 --> 01:07:06.714
You better save some tequila
for breakfast.

01:07:06.814 --> 01:07:09.717
Oh, yeah, that's a good idea. Heh.
Come on in.

01:07:09.817 --> 01:07:12.720
Where in the hell have you been?
I've been waiting.

01:07:12.820 --> 01:07:14.887
- We were at the hospital, Cully.
- CULLY: Oh?

01:07:14.989 --> 01:07:17.773
- Dad had a stroke.
- CULLY: A stroke?

01:07:18.159 --> 01:07:19.769
Really?

01:07:19.869 --> 01:07:22.730
- Is he all right?
- He's gonna be all right.

01:07:22.830 --> 01:07:25.239
CULLY: Oh, I'm sorry, Gwen.

01:07:25.833 --> 01:07:28.945
- God, Cully, you look perfectly awful.
- Oh, I am. I am.

01:07:29.045 --> 01:07:32.782
- I'll get you some supper.
- No, wait, wait, wait. Nothing to eat.

01:07:32.882 --> 01:07:34.284
(GRUNTS)

01:07:34.384 --> 01:07:37.578
I got fired, heh,
so I came by to say goodbye.

01:07:38.346 --> 01:07:42.666
- Fired? What are you talking about?
- Well, see, they were over budget...

01:07:42.767 --> 01:07:45.378
and they wanted to get rid
of some of the deadwood.

01:07:45.478 --> 01:07:48.296
- My Wood's dead. Heh.
- Who fired you? Max?

01:07:48.898 --> 01:07:50.049
Uh...

01:07:50.149 --> 01:07:51.634
I don't really know.

01:07:51.734 --> 01:07:57.021
But I got the word
from that little popcorn fart, Tony.

01:07:58.992 --> 01:08:00.477
- Oh, no, no.
- Shut up.

01:08:00.577 --> 01:08:03.938
Nobody can hire and fire anybody on this...
What are you doing? Come on.

01:08:04.038 --> 01:08:06.774
I told them if they fired you,
they'd have to fire me.

01:08:06.874 --> 01:08:10.278
- Did you tell them that? I appreciate that.
- Yes, I told them that.

01:08:10.378 --> 01:08:14.365
You little rascal. That's why I love you.
We do things for each other.

01:08:14.465 --> 01:08:17.202
- I'm gonna do something for you now.
- Do something for me.

01:08:17.301 --> 01:08:20.120
Good advice. Get off the damn picture
before you get hurt.

01:08:20.220 --> 01:08:23.832
GWEN: Cully, he told me this is his
last picture. After this, no more.

01:08:23.933 --> 01:08:26.877
Oh, sure, if there's anything left of him
after this picture.

01:08:26.978 --> 01:08:29.296
- HOOPER: Cully.
- What does that mean?

01:08:30.106 --> 01:08:32.424
- Oh. You didn't tell her?
- No, I didn't.

01:08:32.524 --> 01:08:34.551
He didn't tell you? Naughty, naughty.

01:08:34.652 --> 01:08:37.930
He didn't tell you
about the big bad rocket-car stunt?

01:08:38.031 --> 01:08:40.767
- Will you stop it?
- No. What stunt?

01:08:40.867 --> 01:08:43.144
Oh. Well, I'm gonna let him
fill in the details.

01:08:43.243 --> 01:08:45.897
Mind your own business.
Just drink your tequila.

01:08:45.997 --> 01:08:49.274
I do want to tell you one thing
while I'm still drunk on your tequila.

01:08:49.375 --> 01:08:52.319
- Shit. Oh, shit.
- I went to see his doctor.

01:08:52.420 --> 01:08:56.490
I went to see his doctor,
asked him what's going to happen to him...

01:08:56.591 --> 01:09:00.245
when he lands that rocket car
over there across the gorge...

01:09:00.345 --> 01:09:03.247
- ...how hard it's gonna hit.
- Sonny, what is he talking about?

01:09:03.348 --> 01:09:06.917
He's talking about $50,000 over and above
what I'll make on this picture.

01:09:07.018 --> 01:09:09.586
Besides, I can't let that kid
do the stunt alone.

01:09:09.687 --> 01:09:11.548
The kid? What...? What is this?

01:09:11.648 --> 01:09:13.758
You've got Ski in this crazy thing now?

01:09:13.858 --> 01:09:17.011
No, Gwenny, it's the other way around.
The kid's got him.

01:09:17.111 --> 01:09:19.895
- Will you butt out?
- I told you that kid was gonna get you killed.

01:09:21.032 --> 01:09:24.475
Sonny, you told me you were quitting
after this picture...

01:09:24.577 --> 01:09:27.395
so you could trade it off
against doing this stunt. True?

01:09:27.497 --> 01:09:30.984
You're crazy, you know that?
I'll tell you one thing. You're crazy.

01:09:31.084 --> 01:09:33.236
- I don't want to hear your...
- CULLY: No!

01:09:33.336 --> 01:09:35.321
- Dumb jackass!
- Shut your drunken mouth!

01:09:35.421 --> 01:09:39.081
- Listen, don't mess up my wardrobe.
- GWEN: Hey! Sonny!

01:09:41.344 --> 01:09:42.786
(CULLY GRUNTS)

01:09:43.470 --> 01:09:44.997
CULLY: Oh.

01:09:45.098 --> 01:09:47.750
Hundred and seventy-two
motion-picture fights.

01:09:47.850 --> 01:09:50.377
That's the first time he ever hit me.

01:09:50.478 --> 01:09:52.839
That son of a bitch can hit. Heh.

01:09:52.939 --> 01:09:56.508
- GWEN: Cully, I'm so sorry.
- Oh, he didn't mean it.

01:09:56.609 --> 01:09:59.393
If he had meant it,
he'd have hit a lot harder.

01:10:00.446 --> 01:10:01.979
He's hurting, Gwenny.

01:10:03.282 --> 01:10:05.975
He's got a lot of things on his mind.

01:10:07.829 --> 01:10:09.862
Oh, Cully.

01:10:15.545 --> 01:10:18.705
- Sonny.
- Mm?

01:10:21.884 --> 01:10:24.122
Sonny, will you go home now?

01:10:28.725 --> 01:10:30.292
Why?

01:10:30.685 --> 01:10:32.593
Please?

01:10:33.187 --> 01:10:34.754
Sonny.

01:10:34.856 --> 01:10:36.468
(HOOPER BLOWS RASPBERRY)

01:10:37.775 --> 01:10:39.302
I'm sorry. Heh, heh.

01:10:39.402 --> 01:10:42.430
Sonny, what are you trying to prove?

01:10:42.530 --> 01:10:45.183
Let me ask you something, Debbie.

01:10:45.283 --> 01:10:47.810
This is a big town, isn't it?

01:10:47.910 --> 01:10:50.979
- I mean, Los Angeles is a big town.
- Yeah.

01:10:51.080 --> 01:10:56.402
Well, why the hell does this bar close
before the bars in Tulsa?

01:10:58.129 --> 01:11:00.162
Can you answer me that?

01:11:00.798 --> 01:11:02.786
I don't know, Sonny.

01:11:03.593 --> 01:11:07.413
Hey, let's go somewhere
and have some breakfast. You want to?

01:11:09.766 --> 01:11:11.629
I can't do that.

01:11:12.185 --> 01:11:14.969
Let's go somewhere and have some lunch.

01:11:15.855 --> 01:11:18.264
I can't do that either.

01:11:19.442 --> 01:11:23.512
Well, let's go somewhere
and jump each other's bones.

01:11:24.280 --> 01:11:26.643
- Aah.
- Hmm?

01:11:27.533 --> 01:11:30.520
- That is tempting, Sonny. Yeah.
- Is it?

01:11:30.620 --> 01:11:33.188
- But you know why I can't do it?
- Why?

01:11:33.289 --> 01:11:38.656
Because my husband
is so jealous and so near.

01:11:40.171 --> 01:11:41.823
And so big.

01:11:41.923 --> 01:11:42.989
MAN: Sonny...

01:11:43.090 --> 01:11:45.157
(HOOPER LAUGHING)

01:11:48.221 --> 01:11:49.997
- MAN: Hey.
- Huh?

01:11:50.097 --> 01:11:53.334
When you get so drunk you make a pass
at Debbie in my presence...

01:11:53.434 --> 01:11:55.586
- ...it's time for me to call you a cab.
- Yeah.

01:11:55.686 --> 01:11:59.215
You don't call me a cab. I am a cab.
You don't need to call me a cab.

01:11:59.315 --> 01:12:04.721
I'm perfectly able
to take a walk or ride...

01:12:04.821 --> 01:12:07.974
or fly or whatever.
Anything you want me to do, I can do.

01:12:08.074 --> 01:12:10.733
- I'm perfectly coordinated.
- Sonny.

01:12:11.160 --> 01:12:14.229
So bye-bye and so long.

01:12:25.216 --> 01:12:27.329
(HORSE NEIGHS)

01:14:15.159 --> 01:14:17.647
(WHINNIES)

01:14:21.248 --> 01:14:22.900
ROGER: You said you could do it.

01:14:23.000 --> 01:14:26.362
I rewrote the script
because you said you could do it.

01:14:26.462 --> 01:14:29.073
We rearranged the shooting schedule.

01:14:29.173 --> 01:14:32.117
We spent a damn fortune
preparing for that stunt...

01:14:32.218 --> 01:14:34.706
because you said you could do it.

01:14:35.179 --> 01:14:38.791
- HOOPER: I was wrong, Roger. I'm sorry.
- You were wrong.

01:14:38.891 --> 01:14:42.295
He was wrong, Max. He's sorry.

01:14:42.395 --> 01:14:47.808
He blows the whole goddamn movie
and he says, "Gee, I was wrong. Sorry."

01:14:49.068 --> 01:14:50.177
(SIGHS)

01:14:50.277 --> 01:14:52.219
Okay, okay. New business.

01:14:52.321 --> 01:14:56.309
- Ski does it with someone else, that's all.
- Why don't you forget it, Roger?

01:14:56.409 --> 01:14:58.351
I never liked the damn gag anyhow.

01:14:58.452 --> 01:15:00.770
- Who else can do the stunt?
- Buddy Joe can do it.

01:15:00.871 --> 01:15:02.899
- He's not available.
- ROGER: Who else?

01:15:02.999 --> 01:15:04.486
Nobody.

01:15:04.959 --> 01:15:09.029
- What do you mean, nobody?
- I mean nobody. It's a very complicated stunt.

01:15:09.130 --> 01:15:12.199
There's maybe three guys that can do it,
and we're not available.

01:15:12.299 --> 01:15:14.366
Ski will do it solo with a dummy, then.

01:15:15.970 --> 01:15:19.790
Goddamn, Roger. If you knew
what the hell you were talking about...

01:15:19.890 --> 01:15:22.293
you'd realize it takes two guys
to do the stunt.

01:15:22.393 --> 01:15:25.086
One guy to drive,
one guy to read the instruments.

01:15:25.187 --> 01:15:27.425
And I'm telling you
that Ski isn't qualified.

01:15:29.525 --> 01:15:32.594
Max, does this man still have a job
on this picture?

01:15:32.695 --> 01:15:35.764
Sonny works here as long as I say so.

01:15:35.865 --> 01:15:38.604
Or as long as Sonny wants to.

01:15:39.160 --> 01:15:40.727
Thank you, Max.

01:15:40.828 --> 01:15:43.731
Now, if Sonny says Ski can't do it,
I believe him.

01:15:43.831 --> 01:15:46.445
It's only a damn movie anyhow,
for God's sake.

01:15:49.253 --> 01:15:51.696
Only a movie?

01:15:51.797 --> 01:15:54.325
I want you to call the studio brass.

01:15:54.425 --> 01:15:57.662
I want you to tell them
and their stockholders, distributors...

01:15:57.762 --> 01:16:00.915
and the bank that it's only a movie.
Will you do that, Max?

01:16:01.015 --> 01:16:04.502
I want you to tell them, "Forget about
all your money. It's only a movie."

01:16:04.602 --> 01:16:08.046
I'll tell them that no damn movie
is worth a man's life!

01:16:09.440 --> 01:16:13.635
And I'll tell them unless I can shoot
this picture the way I want to...

01:16:13.736 --> 01:16:17.351
and that means this stunt,
then I take a walk.

01:16:18.407 --> 01:16:22.477
And we'll see who walks,
Mr. Berns, you or I.

01:16:27.249 --> 01:16:29.282
I'm sorry, Max.

01:16:29.877 --> 01:16:32.780
Ah, what the hell, Sonny. What the hell.

01:16:32.880 --> 01:16:34.572
(HOOPER CHUCKLES)

01:16:35.257 --> 01:16:37.368
You know the old saying:

01:16:37.468 --> 01:16:40.537
BOTH:
You'll never work in this town again.

01:16:40.638 --> 01:16:42.039
- Ha, ha.
- Hmm.

01:16:42.139 --> 01:16:44.000
Unless they need you.

01:16:44.100 --> 01:16:45.917
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

01:16:47.520 --> 01:16:49.462
(COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING)

01:16:58.739 --> 01:17:01.603
- WAITRESS: Here you go, Cully.
- Thanks. A Coke?

01:17:02.284 --> 01:17:04.852
- If you're still mad, I can just leave...
- Shut up and sit down.

01:17:04.954 --> 01:17:06.521
(CULLY CHUCKLES)

01:17:08.582 --> 01:17:11.742
Kind of early in the day
for that hard stuff, isn't it?

01:17:12.503 --> 01:17:15.697
I'm working out my left arm
this morning.

01:17:15.798 --> 01:17:18.867
I'll get around to my right arm
this afternoon.

01:17:19.176 --> 01:17:20.834
(CULLY CHUCKLES)

01:17:21.637 --> 01:17:25.499
You heard what's happening, haven't you?
I'll tell you what's happening.

01:17:25.599 --> 01:17:28.964
That new kid, Ski?
Well, they've got him gaffing the show.

01:17:30.229 --> 01:17:35.009
You know what else? I'll tell you what else.
They canceled that car stunt.

01:17:35.109 --> 01:17:36.469
At least temporarily.

01:17:36.569 --> 01:17:38.971
You were absolutely right,
it's a two-man stunt.

01:17:39.071 --> 01:17:43.434
Ain't nobody crazy enough to ride with that
kid, with a rocket strapped to his butt.

01:17:43.534 --> 01:17:46.687
And you can bet your ass,
your cowboy hat and your house cat...

01:17:46.787 --> 01:17:49.901
they're gonna be coming after you
to get you to do the stunt.

01:17:50.541 --> 01:17:52.358
You gonna do the stunt?

01:17:53.419 --> 01:17:55.578
You know what, Cully?

01:17:57.548 --> 01:18:00.992
There's a whole new breed
of stuntman coming along.

01:18:02.303 --> 01:18:04.041
They're younger and...

01:18:04.847 --> 01:18:06.789
stronger...

01:18:07.933 --> 01:18:10.419
tougher than us.

01:18:10.519 --> 01:18:13.881
They don't take pills,
they don't drink...

01:18:13.981 --> 01:18:17.843
they don't... They don't take shots.

01:18:17.943 --> 01:18:20.761
They use little pocket calculators.

01:18:22.156 --> 01:18:25.691
If we don't watch out, they're gonna
blow us right out of the tub.

01:18:26.994 --> 01:18:29.733
You didn't answer my question.
Are you gonna do the stunt?

01:18:32.708 --> 01:18:34.275
(SIGHS)

01:18:34.376 --> 01:18:38.489
MAX: Boy, I never realized there were
so many gags at the end of the picture.

01:18:38.589 --> 01:18:40.241
So involved.

01:18:40.341 --> 01:18:44.957
Fire gags, the whole town being blown up,
50 stuntmen doing falls.

01:18:48.182 --> 01:18:49.999
All right, Max.

01:18:51.435 --> 01:18:54.296
What's the real reason
you came out here?

01:18:54.396 --> 01:18:57.260
To ask me to come back
and gaff the show?

01:18:58.442 --> 01:19:00.930
No, it's the rocket-car gag, Sonny.

01:19:01.820 --> 01:19:05.850
- The rocket car?
- It's a two-man job, just like you always said.

01:19:05.950 --> 01:19:07.852
Nobody in town will touch it.

01:19:07.952 --> 01:19:11.313
- Roger's worried that Ski will get hurt.
- That's a lot of bullshit.

01:19:11.413 --> 01:19:14.027
Roger's worried about getting his shot.

01:19:14.583 --> 01:19:17.527
Roger's worried about
finishing his picture.

01:19:17.628 --> 01:19:22.369
So he talked you into coming out here
to ask me to come back and do the gag.

01:19:22.883 --> 01:19:25.661
You tell Roger to go sit
on a short stick.

01:19:25.761 --> 01:19:28.414
- If you won't do it for Roger...
- I'll do it for you?

01:19:28.514 --> 01:19:31.332
- I'd appreciate it.
- You'd appreciate it?

01:19:33.811 --> 01:19:37.471
What happened to you, Max?
You used to be tough.

01:19:38.399 --> 01:19:40.466
Nobody could tell you how
to make a picture.

01:19:41.068 --> 01:19:42.885
And nobody got hurt on your pictures.

01:19:42.987 --> 01:19:45.180
If I don't deliver this picture...

01:19:45.281 --> 01:19:49.817
I'll be the producer who blew
the biggest and hottest project in town.

01:19:51.495 --> 01:19:53.856
All washed up. Finished.

01:19:53.956 --> 01:19:57.116
I'm too old to go back
to selling door-to-door.

01:20:13.475 --> 01:20:15.668
Okay, Max.

01:20:18.230 --> 01:20:19.547
You got me.

01:20:43.005 --> 01:20:44.788
GWEN: You gonna do it?

01:20:46.342 --> 01:20:47.784
Yeah.

01:20:50.679 --> 01:20:52.087
I'm gonna do it.

01:20:55.351 --> 01:20:57.919
I won't be here when you get back.

01:21:07.363 --> 01:21:10.056
(DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES)

01:21:11.909 --> 01:21:13.976
(SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

01:21:20.501 --> 01:21:23.194
- JEFFREY: Hey, Sonny! How you doing, my man?
- Jeffrey.

01:21:23.295 --> 01:21:25.322
- Gary.
- GARY: How's it hanging, Sonny?

01:21:25.422 --> 01:21:27.990
- CLIFF: Hi, Sonny. Max said you were coming in.
- Danny.

01:21:28.092 --> 01:21:30.202
Nice to see you back.

01:21:30.302 --> 01:21:32.705
What do you think of my baby?

01:21:32.805 --> 01:21:34.122
It's big.

01:21:34.223 --> 01:21:36.333
Looks like one of King Kong's
suppositories.

01:21:36.433 --> 01:21:38.500
(ALL LAUGH)

01:21:39.228 --> 01:21:42.589
- How you doing, Ski?
- Fine, Sonny. How about you?

01:21:42.689 --> 01:21:44.341
HOOPER: Good.

01:21:44.441 --> 01:21:47.094
Let me tell you guys
how this thing works.

01:21:47.194 --> 01:21:49.637
Now, Sonny, your job
is to dial up the pressure.

01:21:49.738 --> 01:21:54.309
You'll need 1500 pounds,
and that leaves Ski free to drive.

01:21:54.410 --> 01:21:58.647
When the pressure's right,
hit the switch, and you are gone.

01:21:58.747 --> 01:22:01.031
- How's it handle?
- Haven't driven it yet.

01:22:02.501 --> 01:22:04.568
- Let's try it out.
- I heard that.

01:22:09.550 --> 01:22:11.367
(ENGINE STARTS)

01:22:19.059 --> 01:22:20.461
How's it feel?

01:22:20.561 --> 01:22:22.674
Pulls a little to the left.

01:22:23.272 --> 01:22:24.882
Anything else?

01:22:24.982 --> 01:22:27.391
That cigarette lighter don't work.

01:22:29.778 --> 01:22:33.265
You just better hope that
that cigarette lighter works.

01:22:33.365 --> 01:22:34.807
(SKI CHUCKLES)

01:22:40.831 --> 01:22:43.442
SKI:
We'll be following the explosive truck.

01:22:43.542 --> 01:22:45.985
The driver will jump out,
and it'll blow.

01:22:46.086 --> 01:22:49.781
Supposed to collapse the bridge
from the super structure to the other bank.

01:22:53.886 --> 01:22:58.374
You figure out on that pocket calculator
how many G's we're pulling when we land?

01:22:58.474 --> 01:23:00.876
Eight to 10 if we land on our wheels.

01:23:00.976 --> 01:23:03.212
We gotta make sure
we hit the ramp just right...

01:23:03.312 --> 01:23:05.714
otherwise it'd veer off one way
or the other...

01:23:05.814 --> 01:23:07.966
or could just go head
first into that bank.

01:23:08.066 --> 01:23:11.095
- If that happens, there's just one thing to do.
- What's that?

01:23:11.195 --> 01:23:14.434
Put your head between your legs
and kiss your ass goodbye.

01:23:16.658 --> 01:23:18.316
It's a piece of cake.

01:23:18.827 --> 01:23:20.394
(LAUGHS)

01:23:20.496 --> 01:23:21.938
(CHUCKLES)

01:23:24.791 --> 01:23:26.819
I'll buy you a drink.

01:23:26.919 --> 01:23:29.154
You don't drink, do you?

01:23:29.254 --> 01:23:30.864
I'm willing to start.

01:23:30.964 --> 01:23:32.906
Damn good time to do it.

01:23:35.010 --> 01:23:36.952
SKI: You know...

01:23:37.054 --> 01:23:40.958
all this hanging around with you,
I think you're starting to rub off on me.

01:23:41.058 --> 01:23:43.836
- HOOPER: How's that?
- SKI: Well, a couple ways.

01:23:43.936 --> 01:23:45.045
(BURPS)

01:23:45.145 --> 01:23:46.462
- Uh-huh.
- Excuse me.

01:23:46.563 --> 01:23:50.132
My first marriage, you know,
is more than likely in the shitter.

01:23:50.234 --> 01:23:51.767
Oh, yeah.

01:23:52.569 --> 01:23:55.558
And I'm learning to drink and liking it.

01:23:55.948 --> 01:23:58.015
(BOTH LAUGH)

01:23:58.116 --> 01:24:01.060
Yeah, well...

01:24:01.161 --> 01:24:05.106
my present relationship is not good.

01:24:05.207 --> 01:24:07.149
Actually, it's in the shitter too.

01:24:07.251 --> 01:24:09.528
(SKI CHUCKLES)

01:24:09.628 --> 01:24:14.158
Well, what the hell
is it about stuntmen...

01:24:14.258 --> 01:24:16.535
and their wives and relationships?

01:24:16.635 --> 01:24:21.080
I don't know.
It's a little like drinking and driving.

01:24:21.890 --> 01:24:24.418
Eventually there's gonna be
a hell of a wreck.

01:24:24.518 --> 01:24:27.507
- SHERIFF: Hey, guys.
- Hey. Oh, hey.

01:24:28.397 --> 01:24:30.715
- Is this your car?
- Yeah.

01:24:30.816 --> 01:24:33.552
- Looks pretty fast.
- Looks ain't deceiving.

01:24:33.652 --> 01:24:38.807
From the looks of them beer cans,
I'd say you two guys were a little drunk.

01:24:38.907 --> 01:24:42.476
SKI: Like I said,
looks ain't deceiving, you old fart.

01:24:42.578 --> 01:24:44.730
Better let me handle this.

01:24:44.830 --> 01:24:47.691
I hope you guys ain't planning
on doing any more driving.

01:24:47.791 --> 01:24:50.903
We're not gonna do any more driving.
I just called my mother.

01:24:51.003 --> 01:24:54.197
And she's gonna come out here
and pick us up and take us home.

01:24:54.298 --> 01:24:56.491
I'm gonna leave the car here
and go home with her.

01:24:56.592 --> 01:24:57.993
(HOOPER LAUGHS)

01:24:58.093 --> 01:25:00.536
- Your mother?
- Yeah.

01:25:00.637 --> 01:25:01.954
I hope you're right.

01:25:05.726 --> 01:25:07.293
Old fart.

01:25:07.394 --> 01:25:10.547
So the queen says to the photographer:

01:25:10.647 --> 01:25:13.634
"I got a brother-in-law
that's a photographer."

01:25:13.734 --> 01:25:17.262
The photographer says, "So?
I've got a brother-in-law that's a queen."

01:25:17.362 --> 01:25:19.765
(BOTH LAUGHING)

01:25:19.865 --> 01:25:22.518
Oh. Look what we got here.

01:25:22.618 --> 01:25:24.401
Howdy, old fart.

01:25:26.371 --> 01:25:28.564
Afternoon, officer. Nice day, isn't it?

01:25:29.249 --> 01:25:30.736
Pull up, right over there!

01:25:31.293 --> 01:25:34.362
- What's that?
- I said, pull over up front!

01:25:34.463 --> 01:25:37.241
- Pull over up front, that's what I said!
- Gotcha.

01:25:37.341 --> 01:25:38.658
Shall we?

01:25:39.176 --> 01:25:40.242
(SKI CHUCKLES)

01:25:40.344 --> 01:25:42.411
SKI: Say goodbye to the nice officer.

01:25:42.971 --> 01:25:44.629
Bye-bye, nice officer.

01:25:50.395 --> 01:25:52.588
Great God almighty!

01:25:53.899 --> 01:25:55.762
Headquarters!

01:25:57.194 --> 01:25:58.476
Never mind.

01:25:58.737 --> 01:26:00.847
ROGER (OVER RADIO):
All right, Tony, I'm coming down.

01:26:00.947 --> 01:26:03.640
Get Hooper and Ski ready, will you?

01:26:03.742 --> 01:26:06.981
All right, move it out of here.
The helicopter's coming down.

01:26:09.706 --> 01:26:12.399
ROGER:
Tony, do I have to do everything myself?

01:26:12.501 --> 01:26:14.739
Get those people out of here.

01:26:16.755 --> 01:26:19.699
TONY: Hooper! Ski! Get over here.
Roger wants you.

01:26:20.634 --> 01:26:22.827
Let's go, let's go! Over here!

01:26:31.395 --> 01:26:36.387
We'll be putting away this thing here.
We're gonna blow all this up.

01:26:37.984 --> 01:26:43.223
ROGER: As you remember, it's a giant
earthquake, you know, with fires, explosions...

01:26:43.323 --> 01:26:46.810
buildings falling everywhere,
chaos, terror...

01:26:46.910 --> 01:26:49.444
and you'll be driving through it.

01:26:51.498 --> 01:26:54.401
It has a nice grayness, like La Strada.

01:26:54.501 --> 01:26:57.487
All right, I'll be in the chopper
for all of this.

01:26:57.587 --> 01:27:00.656
And we start back there
at the administration building.

01:27:00.757 --> 01:27:03.535
When the earthquake hits,
we collapse the building.

01:27:03.635 --> 01:27:07.247
That's a great idea, Roger.
That's gonna look terrific on film.

01:27:07.347 --> 01:27:09.915
Now, this gas station is where...

01:27:10.892 --> 01:27:15.505
you'll force one of those cars
chasing you to hit those pumps...

01:27:15.605 --> 01:27:18.514
and that'll set off our main tank.

01:27:19.776 --> 01:27:21.386
Sensational idea, Roger.

01:27:21.486 --> 01:27:22.928
It's the only way it can be filmed.

01:27:23.029 --> 01:27:24.346
(SMOOCHES)

01:27:24.781 --> 01:27:26.808
ROGER:
Actually, you're quite wrong, Tony.

01:27:26.908 --> 01:27:30.437
There are several ways of doing it,
but this is undoubtedly the best.

01:27:30.537 --> 01:27:32.439
All right, Sonny, I'm depending on you.

01:27:32.539 --> 01:27:36.984
I want some good stunts, some cars skidding,
other cars crashing into each other...

01:27:37.085 --> 01:27:40.279
but these smokestacks are important.

01:27:40.380 --> 01:27:45.035
When they fall, they demolish everything.
They've got to just miss your car.

01:27:45.135 --> 01:27:47.120
That is crucial...

01:27:47.220 --> 01:27:50.539
because we can't put those stacks
back together again.

01:27:50.640 --> 01:27:52.250
TONY: That's right, Roger.

01:27:52.350 --> 01:27:55.504
Here's where you find the explosives truck
that blows the bridge...

01:27:55.604 --> 01:27:59.094
and of course,
your car will have to jump the river.

01:28:06.656 --> 01:28:09.810
CULLY: We'll go over here where
we can get a good view of the jump.

01:28:09.910 --> 01:28:12.562
- It's good to see you.
- You've come for the jump, right?

01:28:12.662 --> 01:28:14.439
- Yeah.
- It's gonna be neat. Later.

01:28:14.539 --> 01:28:17.818
CULLY:
Hey, Gwen. Gwen. Do you want to see him?

01:28:17.918 --> 01:28:19.451
No.

01:28:20.462 --> 01:28:22.074
Afterward.

01:28:28.011 --> 01:28:30.545
TONY: Roger wants to talk to you guys.

01:28:31.223 --> 01:28:32.749
Yeah, Roger?

01:28:32.849 --> 01:28:35.711
All right, Ski, Sonny, this is Roger.
You boys ready?

01:28:35.811 --> 01:28:39.221
- HOOPER (OVER RADIO): We were born ready.
- Wonderful. Let's try one, shall we?

01:28:40.232 --> 01:28:42.425
One's all you get, hoss.

01:28:42.526 --> 01:28:45.470
- Good luck, guys.
- Hold this while we're gone, will you?

01:28:45.570 --> 01:28:49.435
ROGER: Remember, people, no one ever won
an Oscar for second best. So get ready.

01:28:52.994 --> 01:28:56.773
- All right, this is it. Roll the cameras.
- MAN 1: Speed.

01:28:56.873 --> 01:28:59.609
- MAN 2: Rolling cameras one through five.
- MAN 3: Six through nine.

01:28:59.709 --> 01:29:02.994
- MAN 4: Eleven and 12.
- Action! Go, go, go!

01:29:04.506 --> 01:29:05.948
(TIRES SCREECHING)

01:29:12.264 --> 01:29:14.297
(HORN HONKS)

01:29:24.234 --> 01:29:26.518
We're up to pressure, 1500 pounds.

01:29:34.494 --> 01:29:36.311
Goddamn. Cliff was working overtime.

01:29:41.084 --> 01:29:42.651
(SIREN WAILS)

01:29:45.422 --> 01:29:47.865
We're losing...
We're losing some pressure.

01:29:47.966 --> 01:29:51.535
- Well, stick the thing up to full power!
- I already did that!

01:29:51.636 --> 01:29:53.997
It's down, 1400 pounds.

01:29:54.097 --> 01:29:56.005
- It just ain't enough.
- It better be.

01:29:58.852 --> 01:30:00.009
(CHUCKLES)

01:30:11.531 --> 01:30:13.098
Good, boy. You're doing great.

01:30:35.597 --> 01:30:36.663
Woo-hoo!

01:30:44.230 --> 01:30:47.048
Holy shit. Your speed is right on.

01:30:47.692 --> 01:30:49.759
(BOTH WHOOPING)

01:30:49.861 --> 01:30:51.678
- I love it! I love it! Ha-ha-ha!
- Whoo!

01:30:58.328 --> 01:31:00.270
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

01:31:04.125 --> 01:31:06.443
We're down to 1100 pounds pressure.

01:31:06.544 --> 01:31:08.737
- We're in trouble now.
- Goddamn it, Sonny.

01:31:09.339 --> 01:31:11.953
(ALL SCREAMING)

01:31:30.318 --> 01:31:33.430
One more curve and they're gonna blow
that bridge all to shit!

01:31:33.530 --> 01:31:35.973
Get on it, son!
Put the pedal to the metal!

01:31:45.625 --> 01:31:47.692
HOOPER:
Get onto that explosives truck's ass!

01:31:55.677 --> 01:31:57.460
(TIRES SCREECH)

01:31:59.639 --> 01:32:01.331
What the hell's the matter?

01:32:01.433 --> 01:32:03.796
- Haven't got enough pressure.
- Screw the pressure!

01:32:09.858 --> 01:32:11.800
What is happening?

01:32:13.028 --> 01:32:16.932
What the hell is going on down there?
Keep rolling, goddamn it!

01:32:17.032 --> 01:32:19.267
My life's worth
more than a piece of film.

01:32:19.367 --> 01:32:23.229
I'll tell you exactly what your life is worth.
Your life is worth $50,000.

01:32:23.329 --> 01:32:25.982
The price you put on it
when you got behind this wheel.

01:32:26.082 --> 01:32:29.694
ROGER: Sonny, Ski, if you do not try
to make this jump...

01:32:29.794 --> 01:32:32.658
you'll never work in this town again.
Is that...?

01:32:34.090 --> 01:32:36.701
- We're going, huh?
- We're going, yeah, we're going.

01:32:36.801 --> 01:32:38.664
Heh. You're crazy.

01:32:42.057 --> 01:32:44.042
- I'm gonna hit it.
- Whoo!

01:32:44.142 --> 01:32:45.880
Whoo!

01:32:59.741 --> 01:33:00.853
(ALL CHATTERING)

01:33:01.367 --> 01:33:03.685
I just don't believe it.

01:33:04.079 --> 01:33:09.275
Cut, cut, cut! And print, goddamn it!
Get me down.

01:33:16.591 --> 01:33:19.535
- MAN 1: Get that door open!
- MAN 2: And get that crowbar over here!

01:33:20.386 --> 01:33:23.000
- MAN 3: Let me get in there.
- MAN 4: Can't get it open.

01:33:23.473 --> 01:33:24.790
Get away.

01:33:25.517 --> 01:33:28.005
Sonny, are you all right?

01:33:28.603 --> 01:33:32.514
Sonny, are you all right? Sonny!
Jesus, Sonny!

01:33:36.611 --> 01:33:37.802
(SOBS)

01:33:40.115 --> 01:33:42.433
- Yes, I know, I know, I know.
- He made it across!

01:33:50.208 --> 01:33:51.695
Sonny.

01:33:52.710 --> 01:33:54.197
Sonny.

01:33:58.842 --> 01:34:00.909
MAN 5: Hey, hey, hey!

01:34:01.010 --> 01:34:03.077
(CROWD APPLAUDING AND CHEERING)

01:34:06.683 --> 01:34:09.001
MAN 6: That was a hell of a jump!

01:34:09.102 --> 01:34:11.169
(CROWD CHATTERING)

01:34:30.665 --> 01:34:32.698
CULLY: Make room for Jocko.

01:34:34.460 --> 01:34:38.198
- I'd like to take another look at that spot.
- Yeah, from this side.

01:34:38.298 --> 01:34:41.207
You're just the greatest.
I love you both.

01:34:41.718 --> 01:34:46.414
- Gwen. Gwen, that was his best stunt ever.
- It was his last, Max.

01:34:50.018 --> 01:34:53.132
- CLIFF: Zoom!
- Wild stunt.

01:34:54.355 --> 01:34:56.508
Max, Max, we did it.

01:34:56.608 --> 01:35:00.637
